I initially thought this was about a romantic relationship. Looking into the lyrics, I think this is about the relationship between Ariana & media/press/fans (possibly surrounding the rumours she wrecked a marriage). 'You cling to your paper & pens' = waiting to write an article. 'Wait until you like me again' = when the angle changes and she is revered again by the press.  'Me & my truth we sit in silence' = Not addressing the rumours. 'Know that you made me' = the press and fans made her the success she is. 'I'm not how you paint me' = how she is depicted in the media.
Thank ariana for every emotion that you transmit to us and help us to release. ❤🙏🏻
